com.camerontec.util.datatypes

Class ByteArrayView

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datatypes.ByteArrayView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Recyclable

    public final class ByteArrayView
extends Object
implements Recyclable
    A view over an array of bytes.

    This class is a simple encapsulation of the common idiom of a segment of a byte array.

      • equals

        public static boolean equals(ByteArrayView v1,
                             byte[] v2Array,
                             int v2Offset,
                             int v2Length)
        Test for equality between a ByteArrayView and a byte[].

        The two objects are considered "equal" if the contents of the ByteArrayView is equal to the contents of the segment of the byte[] implied by the specified offset and length.

        Parameters:
        v1 - The ByteArrayView.
        v2Array - The byte array.
        v2Offset - The offset into the byte array.
        v2Length - The length of the byte array.
        Returns:
        True if the two objects are equals, false otherwise.

      • set

        public ByteArrayView set(byte[] array,
                         int offset,
                         int length)
        Set the contents of this view to a segment of the specified byte array.
        Parameters:
        array - The byte array. Must not be null.
        offset - The offset into the byte array. Must be positive and in range.
        length - The length of the byte array. Must be in range relative to the length of the byte array and the specified offset.
        Returns:
        This byte array view.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the byte array is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the offset or the length are out of range.

      • alias

        public ByteArrayView alias(ByteArrayView view)
        Make this view an alias of the specified view.

        On completion both this view and the aliased view share the same byte array.

        Parameters:
        view - The view to be aliased.
        Returns:
        This view.

      • copyFrom

        public ByteArrayView copyFrom(ByteArrayView other)
        Copy the bytes from another view to this view.

        The underlying array is resized if required to be at least as large as the the other view's length.

        Parameters:
        other - The other view. May not be null.
        Returns:
        This view.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the other view is null.

      • move

        public ByteArrayView move(ByteArrayView view)
        Move the contents of the specified view into this view.

        This is similar to alias(ByteArrayView), however, on completion the byte array is not shared - only this view refers to the underlying byte array. The other view is cleared. That is, this call equivalent to: 

           ByteArrayView originalOwner;
   ByteArrayView newOwner;
   ...
   newOwner.alias(originalOwner);
   originalOwner.clear();
        Parameters:
        view - The view to be aliased.
        Returns:
        This view.
